<bibRefCitation author="Casey, T. L." box="[698,840,977,1003]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" pagination="215 - 376" refId="ref4952" refString="Casey, T. L. (1912) Studies on the Longicornia of North America. Memoirs on the Coleoptera, 3, 215 - 376." type="journal article" year="1912">Casey, 1912</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bates, 1872)" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[859,1218,977,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melancholicum">
<emphasis box="[859,1058,977,1004]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. melancholicum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bates, H. W." box="[1073,1210,977,1003]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" pagination="163 - 238" refId="ref4648" refString="Bates, H. W. (1872) On the longicorn Coleoptera of Chontales, Nicaragua. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1872, 163 - 238. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1872. tb 01888. x" type="journal article" year="1872">Bates, 1872</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(White, 1853)" baseAuthorityName="White" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyanomelas">
<emphasis box="[1276,1436,977,1004]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. cyanomelas</emphasis>
(White, 1853)
</taxonomicName>
[this later not included in the key]; “2” Elytral sutural band broader, shiny light or golden green; the long carina on the disc of the elytra is distinct, more finely tomentose and shinier than its surroundings; the space between the carina and the sutural band, with shape of a longitudinal acute band ending on the apex of the elytra, is more strongly tomentose than the lateral areas. Underside lively shining golden-green, indistinctly whitish pubescent, almost glabrous. Dorsal surface green or golden green; the central band and the basal constriction of the pronotum glabrous and shinier than the densely punctate and irregularly transversely grooved disc; this pubescent as the sides of the elytra. Antennae and legs black; pro- and mesofemoral club, as well as the basal third or half of metafemora red. 
<quantity box="[342,464,1265,1291]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" unit="mm" value="29.5" valueMax="33.0" valueMin="26.0">26–33 mm</quantity>
.— 
<collectingCountry box="[496,608,1265,1291]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(coll. Schw.)—“West indies” (Nepperschmidt Hbg.). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1212,1402,1265,1291]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
<taxonomicName authority="Santos-Silva &amp; Schmid, 2021" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Schmid" authorityYear="2021" box="[1212,1332,1265,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1212,1332,1265,1291]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">carinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1338,1402,1265,1291]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
”
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,725,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt, M." box="[355,533,1301,1327]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" pagination="377 - 396" refId="ref5770" refString="Schmidt, M. (1924) Die amerikanischen Callichrominen (Col., Ceramb.) nach systematischen und phylogenetischen Gesichtspunkten dargestellt. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 5, 377 - 396. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 48019240502" type="journal article" year="1924">Schmidt (1924)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Schmid" authorityYear="2021" box="[546,690,1302,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatum">
<emphasis box="[546,690,1302,1328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. carinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would differ from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[907,1028,1301,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euthalia">
<emphasis box="[907,1028,1301,1328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. euthalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see photograph of the 
<typeStatus box="[1298,1401,1301,1327]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">lectotype</typeStatus>
on 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezark, L. G." box="[151,308,1337,1363]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" refId="ref4783" refString="Bezark, L. G. (2021 a) A photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the World. New World Cerambycidae Catalog. Available from: http: // bezbycids. com / byciddb / wdefault. asp? w = n (accessed 12 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Bezark 2021a</bibRefCitation>
) by the metallic sutural band of the elytra broad (narrow in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[998,1119,1337,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euthalia">
<emphasis box="[998,1119,1337,1364]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. euthalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), longitudinal elytral carina distinct and shinier than on its sides (hardly recognizable in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[848,970,1373,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euthalia">
<emphasis box="[848,970,1373,1400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. euthalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and ventral surface golden-green, with indistinct whitish setae, almost glabrous (blue-green, with short brownish setae in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[1091,1213,1409,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euthalia">
<emphasis box="[1091,1213,1409,1436]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. euthalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). These differences seem to be just variations of the same species. Accordingly, we are transferring 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Schmid" authorityYear="2021" box="[1048,1192,1446,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatum">
<emphasis box="[1048,1192,1446,1472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. carinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the synonym of 
<emphasis box="[151,350,1481,1508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
S. h. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[207,350,1481,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holochlorum">holochlorum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[465,585,1481,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euthalia">
<emphasis box="[465,585,1481,1508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. euthalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,725,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt, M." box="[313,489,1517,1543]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" pagination="377 - 396" refId="ref5770" refString="Schmidt, M. (1924) Die amerikanischen Callichrominen (Col., Ceramb.) nach systematischen und phylogenetischen Gesichtspunkten dargestellt. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 5, 377 - 396. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 48019240502" type="journal article" year="1924">Schmidt (1924)</bibRefCitation>
reported that the 
<typeStatus box="[691,789,1518,1544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Schmid" authorityYear="2021" box="[828,972,1518,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatum">
<emphasis box="[828,972,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. carinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were from 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1216,1517,1543]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and “West Indies”, they have been reported only as being from 
<collectingCountry box="[637,747,1553,1579]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis box="[763,803,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">e.g.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blackwelder, R. E." box="[809,1016,1553,1579]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" pagination="551 - 763" refId="ref4896" refString="Blackwelder, R. E. (1946) Checklist of the coleopterous insects of Mexico, Central America, the West Indies and South America. Part 4. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 185, 551 - 763. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.185.4" type="journal article" year="1946">Blackwelder 1946</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A." box="[1027,1171,1553,1579]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" refId="ref5440" refString="Monne, M. A. (2021) Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Neotropical region. Part I. Subfamily Cerambycinae. Available from: https: // cerambycids. com / catalog / (accessed 12 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Monné 2021</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tavakilian, G. L. &amp; Chevillotte, H." pageId="2" pageNumber="581" refId="ref5866" refString="Tavakilian, G. L. &amp; Chevillotte, H. (2021) Titan: base de donnees internationales sur les Cerambycidae ou Longicornes. Version 3.0. Available from: http: // titan. gbif. fr / (accessed 12 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Tavakilian and Chevillotte 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, the type locality of this species is currently 
<collectingCountry box="[898,1008,1589,1615]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and West Indies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,725,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
<bibRefCitation author="Napp, D. S. &amp; Martins, U. R." box="[199,474,1625,1652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" pagination="352" refId="ref5604" refString="Napp, D. S. &amp; Martins, U. R. (2009) Tribo Callichromatini. In: Martins, U. R. (Org.), Cerambycidae sul-americanos (Coleoptera) Taxonomia. Vol. 10. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 223 - 212 + 352." type="book chapter" year="2009">Napp &amp; Martins (2009)</bibRefCitation>
changed the species group name “euthalia” to “euthalium”, probably because 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Callichroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Callichroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is neuter gender. However, Euthalia (from the Greek Ευθαλια) is a feminine proper name. Therefore, it cannot be changed because it is a noun in apposition (ICZN 1999: 31.2.1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,725,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A." box="[352,513,1733,1759]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" refId="ref5440" refString="Monne, M. A. (2021) Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Neotropical region. Part I. Subfamily Cerambycinae. Available from: https: // cerambycids. com / catalog / (accessed 12 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Monné (2021)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Tavakilian, G. L. &amp; Chevillotte, H." box="[566,926,1733,1759]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" refId="ref5866" refString="Tavakilian, G. L. &amp; Chevillotte, H. (2021) Titan: base de donnees internationales sur les Cerambycidae ou Longicornes. Version 3.0. Available from: http: // titan. gbif. fr / (accessed 12 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Tavakilian &amp; Chevillotte (2021)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[978,1076,1734,1760]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Schmid" authorityYear="2021" box="[1112,1255,1734,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatum">
<emphasis box="[1112,1255,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. carinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are deposited at the ZMHB. However, they are not there. The 
<typeStatus box="[661,753,1769,1795]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">syntype</typeStatus>
(s) from 
<collectingCountry box="[846,956,1769,1795]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Colombia</collectingCountry>
belonged to former collection of Bernhard Schwarzer; this collection is now deposited at the Senckenberg Museum Frankfurt/M since 1929/31 (Bernd Jaeger, personal communication). The other 
<typeStatus box="[566,658,1841,1867]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">syntype</typeStatus>
(s) from West Indies belonged to Mr. Nepperschmidt is(are) neither at the ZMHB, and we do not know where it(they) is(are) currently (Bernd Jaeger, personal communication).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,725,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3417106303" country="Peru" location="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="syntype">
There is a specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[502,553,1914,1940]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[571,687,1913,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12. 7–10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1877,1901]" captionTargetBox="[163,1428,190,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[151,1436,181,1853]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. 7–10) Callichroma sp., male identified by Schmidt as C. carinatum (ZMHB): 7) Dorsal habitus, including entire antennae; 8) Dorsal habitus; 9) Head and pronotum; 10) Labels. 11) Callichroma chiriquina, lectotype male, dorsal habitus (By Jesus Santiago Moure). 12) Callichroma opiparum, holotype male, dorsal habitus (By Jesus Santiago Moure)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5726544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5726544/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Figs 7–10</figureCitation>
) in the ZMHB collection, which was identified by Schmidt as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Schmid" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Schwarzerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">S. carinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It agrees well with the 
<typeStatus box="[534,621,1950,1976]" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">syntype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[689,802,1949,1975]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="581">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, except for the absence of transverse pronotal striae. The identity of this specimen needs to be verified in the future
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
